<!DOCTYPE html>
<html dir="ltr" lang="en-US">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title><%= html_title yield(:page_title) %></title>

    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Gruppo' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>

  <%= csrf_meta_tag %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'jquery' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'rails' %>
  <%= open_id_delegation_link_tags(enki_config[:open_id_delegation, :server], enki_config[:open_id_delegation, :delegate]) if enki_config[:open_id_delegation] %>
  <%= yield(:head) %>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="content">
      <div id="header">
      <a href="<%= root_url %>"><%= enki_config[:title] %></a>
      </div>
      <div id="sticky">
So, here’s our blog. But first, a quick word about what this blog is and what it isn’t: We wanted to create a place where we (and anyone else who is interested) can keep track of the work we are doing with others. We have many plans for this blog and the FFI website, but that does not mean we expect the world to come to us. Sam, Paul, and Rick participate in discussions in many places, and we encourage everyone else to do the same. But it’s also true that sometimes people will be curious about the Institute and the Foundation, and may want to see what we have been up to. This space will be a one-stop location for that, offering original posts but also links to discussions elsewhere. We also have a non-profit space at <a href="http://forwardfound.org/blog">Forward Foundation blog</a> .<p>To celebrate the recent film Tron: Legacy we are using a Tron-like theme.</p></div>
      <div id="main">
        <%= yield %>
      </div>
     <div id="navigation">
          <h2>Links</h2>
     <ul>
        <li><a href="http://futureforwardinstitute.com">FFI</a></li>
        <li class="no-margin"><a href="<%= root_url %>archives">Blog archive</a></li>
     </ul>
        <% unless category_links_for_navigation.empty? -%>
          <h2>Categories</h2>
          <ul>
            <% category_links_for_navigation.each do |link| -%>
              <li><%= link_to(link.name, link.url) %></li>
            <% end -%>
          </ul>
        <% end -%>
        <form method="get" id="sform" action="http://www.google.com/search">
          <div>
            <h2><label for="q">Search</label></h2>

            <input type="text" id="q" value="" name="q">
            <input type="hidden" name="sitesearch" value="<%= enki_config[:url] %>">
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div id="footer"><a rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"><img alt="Creative Commons License" style="border-width:0" src="http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-sa/3.0/80x15.png" /></a><br /><span xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" property="dct:title">Future Forward Institute and Forward Foundation blog</span> is licensed under a <a rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License</a>. <%= enki_config[:author, :name] %>. Valid <a href="http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=referer">HTML5</a> and <%= link_to "ATOM", "http://feedvalidator.org/check.cgi?url=#{enki_config[:url]}/posts.atom" %>. Powered by <a href="http://www.enkiblog.com" title="A Ruby on Rails blogging app for the fashionable developer">Enki</a>. Background image originally published <a href="http://en.gentoo-wiki.com/wiki/GIMP_Fractal_Backgrounds">Gentoo wiki</a>.</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
